    teach: {
      heading: 'Second differences are constant',
      body: [
        'In a LINEAR sequence the FIRST DIFFERENCES (between consecutive terms) are constant.',
        'In a QUADRATIC sequence the first differences are NOT constant, but the SECOND differences (the differences of the first differences) ARE constant.',
        'A quadratic sequence has nth term of the form T_n = an^2 + bn + c.',
        'Quick rule: if the constant SECOND difference equals 2k, then a = k. (Second difference = 2 means a = 1; second difference = 4 means a = 2; second difference = 6 means a = 3, etc.)',
        'Once you know a, find b and c by setting T_1 and T_2 equal to the formula and solving the resulting two equations.',
      ],
      example: 'Sequence 2, 5, 10, 17, 26 — first differences 3, 5, 7, 9; second differences 2, 2, 2. So a = 1. T_1: a + b + c = 2 \\to 1 + b + c = 2. T_2: 4a + 2b + c = 5 \\to 4 + 2b + c = 5. Subtract: 3 + b = 3 \\to b = 0, c = 1. So T_n = n^2 + 1.',
    },
    questions: [
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Sequence 1, 4, 9, 16, 25 — what type?',
