  // ───────────────────── L6: Sequences from patterns ───────────────────
  {
    id: 'L6',
    title: 'Lesson 6 · Sequences from patterns',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Count the dots / sticks / shapes; build a table',
      body: [
        'A common style of question shows a SHAPE PATTERN (matchsticks forming triangles, dots arranged in squares, …) and asks for a formula in terms of the pattern number.',
        'Strategy: (1) count carefully for the first 3-4 patterns; (2) build a table with pattern number n in one row and the count in the next; (3) decide if the count is LINEAR (constant first difference) or QUADRATIC (constant second difference); (4) find the nth term.',
        'For a LINEAR pattern of matchsticks T_n = an + b:',
