        'To simplify \\sqrt{N}: find the largest perfect square that divides N, write N = (perfect square) × (rest), then \\sqrt{N} = \\sqrt{perfect sq} \\times \\sqrt{rest} = (root of perfect sq) \\times \\sqrt{rest}.',
