  // ───────────────────── L11: Adding and subtracting surds ─────────────
  {
    id: 'L11',
    title: 'Lesson 11 · Adding & subtracting surds',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Same surd \\to combine coefficients (like algebra)',
      body: [
        'You can ADD or SUBTRACT surds only if they are the SAME surd. Treat the surd like an algebraic letter and combine coefficients.',
        '2\\sqrt{3} + 5\\sqrt{3} = 7\\sqrt{3}, just as 2x + 5x = 7x.',
        'But 2\\sqrt{3} + 5\\sqrt{2} CANNOT be combined (different surds).',
        'TIP: SIMPLIFY each surd FIRST, because two surds that look different may simplify to the same surd. For example, \\sqrt{8} + \\sqrt{2} = 2\\sqrt{2} + \\sqrt{2} = 3\\sqrt{2}.',
