        'When numbers in front are present (like 2\\sqrt{3} \\times 4\\sqrt{5}), multiply the integers separately and the surds separately: 2 \\times 4 \\times \\sqrt{3} \\times \\sqrt{5} = 8\\sqrt{15}.',
        'Then SIMPLIFY the result if possible.',
      ],
      example: '2\\sqrt{6} \\times 3\\sqrt{2} = 6\\sqrt{12} = 6 \\times 2\\sqrt{3} = 12\\sqrt{3}.',
