  // ───────────────────── L11: Expanding double brackets ────────────────
  {
    id: 'L11',
    title: 'Lesson 11 · Expanding double brackets',
    teach: {
      heading: 'FOIL: First, Outside, Inside, Last',
      body: [
        '(a + b)(c + d) = ac + ad + bc + bd. Each term in the FIRST bracket multiplies each term in the SECOND.',
        'A useful mnemonic is FOIL: First (a \\times c), Outside (a \\times d), Inside (b \\times c), Last (b \\times d).',
        'COLLECT LIKE TERMS at the end (the middle two terms often combine).',
        'Watch signs: (x - 3)(x + 5) = x^2 + 5x - 3x - 15 = x^2 + 2x - 15.',
      ],
      example: '(x + 3)(x + 5) = x^2 + 5x + 3x + 15 = x^2 + 8x + 15.',
    },
    questions: [
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + 2)(x + 3) = ?',
        options: ['x^2 + 5x + 6', 'x^2 + 6x + 5', 'x^2 + 6', 'x^2 + 5'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'x^2 + 3x + 2x + 6.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + 4)(x + 1) = ?',
        options: ['x^2 + 5x + 4', 'x^2 + 4x + 5', 'x^2 + 5', 'x^2 + 4'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'x^2 + x + 4x + 4.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + 7)(x - 2) = ?',
        options: ['x^2 + 5x - 14', 'x^2 - 5x + 14', 'x^2 + 9x - 14', 'x^2 - 14'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'x^2 - 2x + 7x - 14.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x - 3)(x - 5) = ?',
        options: ['x^2 - 8x + 15', 'x^2 + 8x + 15', 'x^2 - 8x - 15', 'x^2 - 2x + 15'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'x^2 - 5x - 3x + 15.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(2x + 1)(x + 3) = ?',
        options: ['2x^2 + 7x + 3', '2x^2 + 4x + 3', '2x^2 + 3x + 7', '2x^2 + x + 3'], correct: 0,
        solution: '2x^2 + 6x + x + 3.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + 5)(x - 5) = ?',
        options: ['x^2 - 25', 'x^2 + 25', 'x^2 - 10x - 25', 'x^2 + 10x'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Difference of squares: middle terms cancel.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(2x + 3)(2x - 3) = ?',
        options: ['4x^2 - 9', '4x^2 + 9', '4x^2 - 12x - 9', '2x^2 - 9'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Difference of squares: 4x^2 - 9.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x - 6)(x + 4) = ?',
        options: ['x^2 - 2x - 24', 'x^2 + 2x - 24', 'x^2 - 24', 'x^2 - 10x + 24'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'x^2 + 4x - 6x - 24.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(3x - 1)(x + 2) = ?',
        options: ['3x^2 + 5x - 2', '3x^2 + 7x - 2', '3x^2 - 2', '3x^2 + 5x + 2'], correct: 0,
        solution: '3x^2 + 6x - x - 2.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + a)(x + b) = ?',
        options: ['x^2 + (a + b)x + ab', 'x^2 + ab', 'x^2 + 2abx', 'x^2 + (ab)x'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'General formula.' },
    ],
  },

  // ───────────────────── L12: Squaring binomials & specials ────────────
  {
    id: 'L12',
    title: 'Lesson 12 · Squaring a binomial',
    teach: {
      heading: '(a + b)^2 = a^2 + 2ab + b^2',
      body: [
        'A SQUARE of a binomial: (a + b)^2 means (a + b)(a + b). Expanding gives a^2 + 2ab + b^2 — square the first, double the product, square the last.',
        'Likewise (a - b)^2 = a^2 - 2ab + b^2.',
        'Common mistake: writing (a + b)^2 = a^2 + b^2 — this is WRONG (you forget the 2ab cross term).',
        'These special-case identities save time and are easy to use in reverse for factorising perfect-square trinomials.',
      ],
      example: '(x + 4)^2 = x^2 + 8x + 16. (3x - 2)^2 = 9x^2 - 12x + 4.',
    },
    questions: [
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + 3)^2 = ?',
        options: ['x^2 + 6x + 9', 'x^2 + 9', 'x^2 + 3x + 9', 'x^2 + 6 + 9'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'a^2 + 2ab + b^2.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x - 5)^2 = ?',
        options: ['x^2 - 10x + 25', 'x^2 + 10x + 25', 'x^2 - 25', 'x^2 - 5x + 25'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Negative sign of b carries through to -2ab.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + 7)^2 = ?',
        options: ['x^2 + 14x + 49', 'x^2 + 49', 'x^2 + 7x + 49', 'x^2 + 14 + 49'], correct: 0,
        solution: '2 \\times 7 = 14.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(2x + 1)^2 = ?',
        options: ['4x^2 + 4x + 1', '2x^2 + 4x + 1', '4x^2 + 2x + 1', '4x^2 + 1'], correct: 0,
        solution: '(2x)^2 + 2(2x)(1) + 1^2.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(3y - 4)^2 = ?',
        options: ['9y^2 - 24y + 16', '9y^2 + 24y + 16', '9y^2 - 16', '9y^2 - 12y + 16'], correct: 0,
        solution: '(3y)^2 - 2(3y)(4) + 16.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(a + b)(a - b) = ?',
        options: ['a^2 - b^2', 'a^2 + b^2', 'a^2 - 2ab + b^2', 'a^2 - 2ab - b^2'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Difference of squares.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + 5)(x - 5) = ?',
        options: ['x^2 - 25', 'x^2 + 25', 'x^2 + 10x - 25', 'x^2 - 10x'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'a^2 - b^2.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(2x + 3y)^2 = ?',
        options: ['4x^2 + 12xy + 9y^2', '4x^2 + 9y^2', '4x^2 + 6xy + 9y^2', '4x^2 + 9y^2 + 12xy'], correct: 3,
        solution: '4x^2 + 12xy + 9y^2 — A and D are equal (just different order).' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: '(x + a)^2 - (x - a)^2 = ?',
        options: ['4ax', '0', '2a^2', '4x^2'], correct: 0,
        solution: '(x^2 + 2ax + a^2) - (x^2 - 2ax + a^2) = 4ax.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Common error: (x + 2)^2 = x^2 + 4. Why is this wrong?',
        options: ['Forgets the cross term 2 \\cdot x \\cdot 2 = 4x', 'Wrong sign', 'Forgets the constant', 'It is right'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Correct expansion is x^2 + 4x + 4.' },
    ],
  },

  // ───────────────────── L13: Factorising x^2 + bx + c ─────────────────
  {
    id: 'L13',
    title: 'Lesson 13 · Factorising x^2 + bx + c',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Find two numbers that multiply to c and add to b',
      body: [
        'To factorise x^2 + bx + c into (x + p)(x + q):',
        'Step 1: Find two numbers p and q such that p \\times q = c AND p + q = b.',
        'Step 2: Write the answer as (x + p)(x + q).',
        'Sign rules: if c is POSITIVE, both p and q have the SAME sign (both positive if b > 0; both negative if b < 0). If c is NEGATIVE, p and q have OPPOSITE signs (and the larger absolute value matches the sign of b).',
        'Always CHECK by multiplying back out.',
      ],
      example: 'x^2 + 7x + 12 = (x + 3)(x + 4) (since 3 \\times 4 = 12 and 3 + 4 = 7).',
    },
    questions: [
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 + 5x + 6.',
        options: ['(x + 2)(x + 3)', '(x + 1)(x + 6)', '(x - 2)(x - 3)', '(x + 5)(x + 1)'], correct: 0,
        solution: '2 \\times 3 = 6, 2 + 3 = 5.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 + 8x + 12.',
        options: ['(x + 2)(x + 6)', '(x + 3)(x + 4)', '(x + 4)(x + 3)', '(x + 12)(x + 1)'], correct: 0,
        solution: '2 \\times 6 = 12, 2 + 6 = 8.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 + 10x + 21.',
        options: ['(x + 3)(x + 7)', '(x + 1)(x + 21)', '(x + 7)(x + 14)', '(x - 3)(x - 7)'], correct: 0,
        solution: '3 \\times 7 = 21, 3 + 7 = 10.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 - 6x + 8.',
        options: ['(x - 2)(x - 4)', '(x + 2)(x + 4)', '(x - 1)(x - 8)', '(x - 8)(x + 1)'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Both negative since c > 0 and b < 0; -2 \\times -4 = 8, -2 + -4 = -6.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 + 2x - 15.',
        options: ['(x + 5)(x - 3)', '(x - 5)(x + 3)', '(x + 5)(x + 3)', '(x - 15)(x + 1)'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'c < 0 \\to opposite signs; 5 \\times -3 = -15, 5 + (-3) = 2.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 - 5x - 6.',
        options: ['(x - 6)(x + 1)', '(x + 6)(x - 1)', '(x - 3)(x - 2)', '(x - 2)(x + 3)'], correct: 0,
        solution: '-6 \\times 1 = -6, -6 + 1 = -5.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 + 7x + 12.',
        options: ['(x + 3)(x + 4)', '(x + 2)(x + 6)', '(x + 12)(x + 1)', '(x + 4)(x + 4)'], correct: 0,
        solution: '3 \\times 4 = 12, 3 + 4 = 7.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 + x - 12.',
        options: ['(x + 4)(x - 3)', '(x - 4)(x + 3)', '(x + 4)(x + 3)', '(x + 12)(x - 1)'], correct: 0,
        solution: '4 \\times -3 = -12, 4 + (-3) = 1.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 - 9x + 20.',
        options: ['(x - 4)(x - 5)', '(x + 4)(x + 5)', '(x - 5)(x + 4)', '(x - 1)(x - 20)'], correct: 0,
        solution: '-4 \\times -5 = 20, -4 + -5 = -9.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Factorise x^2 - 13x + 42.',
        options: ['(x - 6)(x - 7)', '(x - 14)(x - 3)', '(x + 6)(x + 7)', '(x - 21)(x - 2)'], correct: 0,
        solution: '-6 \\times -7 = 42, -6 + -7 = -13.' },
