  // ───────────────────── L2: Pythagoras — shorter side ──────────────────
  {
    id: 'L2',
    title: 'Lesson 2 · Pythagoras: find a shorter side',
    teach: {
      heading: 'a^2 = c^2 - b^2',
      body: [
        'When you know the hypotenuse and one of the legs, REARRANGE Pythagoras to find the missing leg.',
        'a^2 + b^2 = c^2 \\to a^2 = c^2 - b^2 \\to a = \\sqrt{c^2 - b^2}.',
        'Always SUBTRACT the smaller-squared from the bigger-squared (which is the hypotenuse squared) — never the other way around.',
        'If you get a negative under the square root, you have made an error (likely confused which side is the hypotenuse).',
