  // ───────────────────── L6: What makes triangles similar ───────────────
  {
    id: 'L6',
    title: 'Lesson 6 · What makes triangles similar?',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Same shape, different size — angles equal, sides in ratio',
      body: [
        'Two triangles are SIMILAR if they have the same shape (one is a scaled copy of the other).',
        'Equivalent conditions for similarity:',
        '(1) Corresponding ANGLES are equal.',
        '(2) Corresponding sides are in the same RATIO (scale factor).',
        'For triangles, having two pairs of corresponding angles equal is enough (the third pair is automatically equal because angles add to 180°).',
        'When you state similarity, list the vertex letters in CORRESPONDING order, e.g. \\triangle ABC \\sim \\triangle DEF means A↔D, B↔E, C↔F.',
      ],
      example: 'A right triangle with legs 3, 4 (hyp 5) is similar to a right triangle with legs 6, 8 (hyp 10) — sides in ratio 1 : 2.',
    },
    questions: [
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Two similar triangles have all corresponding sides in ratio …',
        options: ['the same (one common scale factor)', 'always 1', 'always 2', 'unrelated'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Definition of similarity.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'If two angles of one triangle equal two angles of another, the triangles are …',
        options: ['Similar', 'Congruent', 'Equal area', 'Identical'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Two pairs equal \\to third pair equal \\to similar.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Triangles with sides 3, 4, 5 and 9, 12, 15 — similar?',
        options: ['Yes (ratio 1:3)', 'No', 'Only if right-angled', 'Cannot tell'], correct: 0,
        solution: '9/3 = 12/4 = 15/5 = 3.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Similar triangles have …',
        options: ['equal corresponding angles AND sides in ratio', 'equal sides only', 'equal angles only — no condition on sides', 'equal areas'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Both conditions are equivalent and characterise similarity.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'If \\triangle ABC \\sim \\triangle DEF, which side corresponds to AB?',
        options: ['DE', 'EF', 'DF', 'Cannot tell'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Vertices in matching order: A↔D, B↔E.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Triangles with angles 30°, 60°, 90° and 30°, 60°, 90° are …',
