  // ───────────────────── L7: Unknown sides in similar triangles ─────────
  {
    id: 'L7',
    title: 'Lesson 7 · Unknown sides in similar triangles',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Set up a ratio between corresponding sides',
      body: [
        'Once two triangles are known to be similar, EVERY pair of corresponding sides is in the same ratio (the scale factor).',
        'Strategy: identify a pair of CORRESPONDING sides whose lengths are both known. Their ratio is the scale factor k.',
        'Then any unknown side = (corresponding known side in the other triangle) × k.',
        'TIP: line up the triangles\\u2019 vertices in correspondence order before writing ratios.',
      ],
      example: 'Two similar triangles. Smaller has side 3, larger has corresponding side 6 — scale factor k = 2. If smaller has another side 5, larger has 5 × 2 = 10.',
