      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'In \\triangle ABC, line DE is parallel to BC and divides AB and AC. Triangles ADE and ABC are …',
        options: ['Similar', 'Congruent', 'Equal area', 'Always equilateral'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Parallel-line construction creates similar triangles.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Triangle ABC: line DE || BC, with AD = 2, DB = 3 (so AB = 5). DE = 4. BC = ?',
        options: ['10', '6', '8', '12'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'k = AB/AD = 5/2; BC = 4 × 5/2 = 10.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'A ramp 5 m long meets the ground at angle θ. A model ramp similar in shape is 2 m long. What\\u2019s the model\\u2019s scale factor?',
        options: ['\\frac{2}{5}', '\\frac{5}{2}', '5', '2'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Model length / original length.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Two similar maps. Original 1:50 000; compare to a 1:25 000 map of the same area. Area ratio?',
        options: ['4:1 (the larger-scale map shows 4× the detail / area on paper)', '2:1', '1:2', '1:4'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Linear ratio 2; area ratio 4.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'In \\triangle ABC, line DE || BC, AD = 4, AB = 12, BC = 9. DE?',
        options: ['3', '4', '6', '12'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'k = AD/AB = 4/12 = 1/3; DE = 9 × 1/3 = 3.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'A photograph and a poster are similar rectangles. Photo: 4 × 6 inches. Poster height: 24 inches. Width?',
        options: ['16 inches', '32 inches', '12 inches', '20 inches'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'k = 24/6 = 4; width = 4 × 4 = 16.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Find length AC in similar triangles where AB = 3, BC = 4, A\\u2019B\\u2019 = 9, B\\u2019C\\u2019 = 12, A\\u2019C\\u2019 = 15. Then AC = ?',
        options: ['5', '6', '15', '\\frac{15}{3}'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'k = 3 (small \\to big); AC = 15/3 = 5.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'A 2.4 m fence casts a 1.6 m shadow; a building casts an 18 m shadow at the same time. Building height?',
        options: ['27 m', '12 m', '9 m', '36 m'], correct: 0,
        solution: '2.4 × 18 / 1.6 = 27.' },
    ],
  },

  // ───────────────────── L9: Scale factors length / area / volume ───────
  {
    id: 'L9',
    title: 'Lesson 9 · Linear, area & volume scale factors',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Length × k → Area × k^2 → Volume × k^3',
      body: [
        'Two SIMILAR shapes are related by a single LINEAR scale factor k. If you scale every length by k:',
        'AREA scales by k^2 (because area = length × length).',
        'VOLUME scales by k^3 (length × length × length).',
        'In reverse: if you know the AREA scale factor is A, the linear scale factor is \\sqrt{A}; if the VOLUME scale factor is V, the linear scale factor is \\sqrt[3]{V} = V^{1/3}.',
      ],
      example: 'A small cube has side 2; the larger has side 6. Linear k = 3. Areas: 4 → 36 (×9 = 3²). Volumes: 8 → 216 (×27 = 3³).',
    },
    questions: [
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Linear scale factor 3. Area scale factor?',
        options: ['9', '3', '27', '6'], correct: 0,
        solution: '3^2 = 9.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Linear scale factor 4. Volume scale factor?',
        options: ['64', '16', '4', '12'], correct: 0,
        solution: '4^3 = 64.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Area scale factor 25. Linear scale factor?',
        options: ['5', '12.5', '625', '\\sqrt{50}'], correct: 0,
        solution: '\\sqrt{25} = 5.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Volume scale factor 125. Linear scale factor?',
        options: ['5', '25', '11.18', '5\\sqrt{5}'], correct: 0,
        solution: '\\sqrt[3]{125} = 5.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'A model is \\frac{1}{50} the size of the actual building. Volume ratio (model : actual)?',
        options: ['1 : 125 000', '1 : 50', '1 : 2 500', '1 : 50^4'], correct: 0,
        solution: '\\frac{1}{50^3} = \\frac{1}{125 000}.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'A photograph 4 × 6 in is enlarged to 12 × 18 in. Area ratio of new : old?',
        options: ['9 : 1', '3 : 1', '6 : 1', '27 : 1'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Linear k = 3; area k = 9.' },
      { kind: 'fill-num', prompt: 'Linear scale factor 6. Volume scale factor?', answer: 216,
        solution: '6^3 = 216.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Two similar cans. Big can is 3× the height of small. Volume ratio big:small?',
        options: ['27 : 1', '9 : 1', '3 : 1', '6 : 1'], correct: 0,
        solution: '3^3 = 27.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Two similar cubes have surface areas 36 and 144. Linear scale factor (small → big)?',
        options: ['2', '4', '6', '12'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Area ratio 4 \\to linear ratio 2.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'A cone with radius 2 has volume 12. A similar cone with radius 6 has volume?',
        options: ['324', '108', '36', '72'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'k = 3; volume k = 27; 12 × 27 = 324.' },
    ],
  },

  // ───────────────────── L10: Areas of similar shapes ───────────────────
  {
    id: 'L10',
    title: 'Lesson 10 · Areas of similar shapes',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Area_2 = Area_1 \\times k^2',
      body: [
        'Once you know two shapes are similar, the ratio of their AREAS is the SQUARE of the linear scale factor.',
        '\\frac{Area_2}{Area_1} = \\left(\\frac{length_2}{length_1}\\right)^2 = k^2.',
        'Strategy: find k from a pair of corresponding lengths, square it, then multiply (or divide) the known area.',
        'In reverse: if you know the area ratio, take the square root for the linear ratio.',
      ],
      example: 'Two similar shapes. Linear ratio 2:3 \\to area ratio 4:9. If small area is 16, large area is 16 × \\frac{9}{4} = 36.',
    },
    questions: [
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Two similar shapes, linear ratio 1:2. Area ratio?',
        options: ['1:4', '1:2', '1:8', '2:1'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Square the linear.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Linear ratio 2:5. Area ratio?',
        options: ['4:25', '2:5', '8:125', '4:5'], correct: 0,
        solution: '2^2 : 5^2.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Smaller similar triangle has area 4 cm^2; larger has area 36 cm^2. Linear scale factor?',
        options: ['3', '9', '6', '\\sqrt{32}'], correct: 0,
        solution: '\\sqrt{36/4} = 3.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Smaller similar shape area 5 cm^2; linear ratio 1:4. Larger area?',
        options: ['80 cm^2', '20 cm^2', '40 cm^2', '125 cm^2'], correct: 0,
        solution: '5 × 16 = 80.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Similar shapes. Smaller has area 24 cm^2 and length 3 cm; larger has corresponding length 12 cm. Larger area?',
        options: ['384 cm^2', '96 cm^2', '288 cm^2', '48 cm^2'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'k = 4, k^2 = 16, 24 × 16 = 384.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Two similar circles. Radii 4 and 6. Area ratio (small : large)?',
        options: ['4 : 9', '2 : 3', '4 : 6', '8 : 27'], correct: 0,
        solution: '(4/6)^2 = 16/36 = 4/9.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Larger similar shape area 72 cm^2; linear scale factor (large→small) 1/3. Smaller area?',
        options: ['8 cm^2', '24 cm^2', '648 cm^2', '36 cm^2'], correct: 0,
        solution: '72 × (1/3)^2 = 72/9 = 8.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Similar shapes — area scale factor 9. Linear scale factor?',
        options: ['3', '9', '4.5', '81'], correct: 0,
        solution: '\\sqrt{9} = 3.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Area ratio 49:9. Linear ratio?',
        options: ['7:3', '49:9', '7:9', 'Cannot tell'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'Square roots.' },
      { kind: 'fill-num', prompt: 'Linear scale factor 5; area of small shape is 7. Larger area?', answer: 175,
        solution: '7 × 25 = 175.' },
