  },

  // ───────────────────── L12: Composite & word problems ─────────────────
  {
    id: 'L12',
    title: 'Lesson 12 · Word problems · similar shapes',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Pick the right power of k for the question',
      body: [
        'Real questions often mix linear, area, and volume quantities. Think about which power of k applies to each:',
        'Lengths, perimeters, distances → multiply by k.',
        'Areas (surface area, painted area, cross-section) → multiply by k^2.',
        'Volumes (capacity, weight if same density, amount of material) → multiply by k^3.',
        'Useful trick: if two shapes are similar with given AREAS, find k = \\sqrt{area ratio} first, then use it for everything else.',
      ],
      example: 'Two similar paintings. Small area 48 cm^2; large area 108 cm^2. AC in small is 4 cm. Diagonal AC in large = ? \\frac{Areas} = \\frac{lengths^2} \\to (\\frac{AC_{big}}{4})^2 = \\frac{108}{48} = \\frac{9}{4} \\to AC_{big} = 4 × \\frac{3}{2} = 6 cm.',
    },
    questions: [
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Two similar paintings. Areas 48 and 108 cm². The smaller has diagonal 4 cm. The larger\\u2019s diagonal?',
        options: ['6 cm', '9 cm', '12 cm', '4 cm'], correct: 0,
        solution: 'k^2 = 108/48 = 9/4 \\to k = 3/2; 4 × 3/2 = 6.' },
      { kind: 'mcq', prompt: 'Two similar bottles, heights 10 cm and 15 cm. Smaller holds 200 ml. Larger?',
        options: ['675 ml', '300 ml', '450 ml', '500 ml'], correct: 0,
