    id: 'L7',
    title: 'Lesson 7 · Upper & lower bounds — basics',
    teach: {
      heading: 'Choose bounds carefully when computing with measurements',
      body: [
        'Each measurement has an upper bound (UB) and a lower bound (LB).',
        'When you ADD: largest sum = UB + UB; smallest sum = LB + LB.',
        'When you SUBTRACT (a \\u2013 b): largest = UB(a) \\u2013 LB(b); smallest = LB(a) \\u2013 UB(b).',
        'Worked example: a = 3.6 (1 d.p.) and b = 14 (nearest 1). a interval [3.55, 3.65); b interval [13.5, 14.5).',
