        '\\frac{a}{\\sin A} = \\frac{b}{\\sin B} = \\frac{c}{\\sin C}.',
        'Use sine rule when you know:',
        'TWO ANGLES + any side: find any other side.',
        'TWO SIDES + the angle OPPOSITE one of them: find the angle opposite the other side.',
        'Watch the AMBIGUOUS CASE (SSA): may give 0, 1, or 2 valid triangles.',
      ],
      example: 'Triangle with A = 50°, B = 60°, a = 8. Then b = 8 sin 60° / sin 50° ≈ 9.05.',
    },
    questions: [
